The paper discusses the impact of mobile nodes arrival patterns in MANETs (Mobile Ad-hoc Networks) using Poisson models. This topic falls under the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of information technology (cs.IT) in MANETs. The study involves analyzing the impact of node arrival patterns on the network's performance, which falls under the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also uses mathematical models to analyze the data, which falls under the sub-category of Mathematical Software (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of node arrival patterns on the network's stability and reliability, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
